it's historical evidence proof that Jesus was born.

265
00:11:50,839 --> 00:11:52,939
And I'm so thankful that he came

266
00:11:52,939 --> 00:11:55,179
and it was exactly on time.

267
00:11:55,179 --> 00:11:57,079
Isaiah seven says this,

268
00:11:57,079 --> 00:11:57,919
as you consider,

269
00:11:57,919 --> 00:12:01,639
continue to think about the great promise of Christ's birth

270
00:12:01,639 --> 00:12:03,199
and you read in the book of Isaiah,

271
00:12:03,199 --> 00:12:04,579
we'll actually look in chapter seven

272
00:12:04,579 --> 00:12:06,439
and also in chapter number nine

273
00:12:06,439 --> 00:12:10,239
and understand this great proclamation that is made

274
00:12:10,239 --> 00:12:12,939
with regard to the birth of Messiah.

275
00:12:12,939 --> 00:12:16,899
And then we'll look at the fulfillment in the New Testament.

276
00:12:16,899 --> 00:12:19,179
But in Isaiah chapter seven,

277
00:12:19,179 --> 00:12:21,799
the Bible says this in verse number 14,

278
00:12:21,799 --> 00:12:26,559
therefore, the Lord himself shall give you a sign.

279
00:12:26,559 --> 00:12:31,559
Behold, a virgin shall conceive and bear a son

280
00:12:31,839 --> 00:12:35,519
and shall call his name Emmanuel.

281
00:12:35,519 --> 00:12:37,199
Isn't that precious?

282
00:12:37,199 --> 00:12:41,199
Some of the modern versions today change that word virgin

283
00:12:41,199 --> 00:12:42,759
for a young maid.

284
00:12:42,759 --> 00:12:44,879
Can I tell you this morning that a virgin and a young maid

285
00:12:44,879 --> 00:12:46,179
are not the same thing?

286
00:12:47,479 --> 00:12:48,479
Amen.

287
00:12:48,479 --> 00:12:50,739
Why is the virgin birth so important?

288
00:12:50,739 --> 00:12:54,099
Because it was necessary that he have no sin nature.

289
00:12:54,099 --> 00:12:56,819
It's a critical truth of God's word.

290
00:12:56,819 --> 00:12:59,619
And here we find that this would be a sign

291
00:12:59,619 --> 00:13:01,019
and it says that,

292
00:13:01,019 --> 00:13:03,859
and shall call his name Emmanuel.

293
00:13:03,859 --> 00:13:04,919
Notice in chapter nine,

294
00:13:04,919 --> 00:13:06,619
before we run to the New Testament,

295
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:08,819
in Isaiah chapter nine,

296
00:13:08,819 --> 00:13:09,899
in verse number six,

297
00:13:09,899 --> 00:13:11,679
the Bible says this,

298
00:13:11,679 --> 00:13:14,819
for unto us a child is born,

299
00:13:14,819 --> 00:13:17,939
unto us a son is given

300
00:13:17,939 --> 00:13:21,699
and the government shall be upon his shoulder

301
00:13:21,699 --> 00:13:24,579
and his name shall be called Wonderful,

302
00:13:24,579 --> 00:13:27,579
Counselor, the Mighty God,

303
00:13:27,579 --> 00:13:29,619
the Everlasting Father,

304
00:13:29,619 --> 00:13:31,619
the Prince of Peace.

305
00:13:31,619 --> 00:13:34,119
Of the increase of his government and peace,

306
00:13:34,119 --> 00:13:35,779
there shall be no end.

307
00:13:35,779 --> 00:13:39,239
Upon the throne of David and upon his kingdom to order it

308
00:13:39,239 --> 00:13:41,499
and to establish it with judgment

309
00:13:41,499 --> 00:13:44,859
and with justice from henceforth even forever,

310
00:13:44,859 --> 00:13:49,539
the zeal of the Lord of hosts will perform this.

311
00:13:49,539 --> 00:13:52,659
The promise of the fulfillment of the Davidic covenant

312
00:13:52,659 --> 00:13:54,579
is in view in verse number seven.

313
00:13:54,579 --> 00:13:56,899
And one day Jesus Christ,

314
00:13:56,899 --> 00:13:59,699
when he returns after the rapture

315
00:13:59,699 --> 00:14:01,219
in the seven year tribulation,

316
00:14:01,219 --> 00:14:03,459
there's going to be a millennial reign

317
00:14:03,459 --> 00:14:07,139
and Jesus Christ himself is going to rule and reign

318
00:14:07,139 --> 00:14:09,699
for a thousand years,

319
00:14:09,699 --> 00:14:14,699
fulfilling the prophecy of the Davidic covenant.

320
00:14:14,899 --> 00:14:16,819
And I'm thankful for that.

321
00:14:16,819 --> 00:14:18,419
You notice in the book of Matthew,

322
00:14:18,419 --> 00:14:20,879
again, the great promise of Christ's birth

323
00:14:20,879 --> 00:14:24,019
and you think about these wonderful declarations

324
00:14:24,019 --> 00:14:25,279
in the Old Testament,

325
00:14:25,279 --> 00:14:27,699
but then you see their fulfillment in the New Testament,

326
00:14:27,699 --> 00:14:29,459
Matthew chapter number one.

327
00:14:30,719 --> 00:14:32,779
And it's a familiar passage,

328
00:14:32,779 --> 00:14:34,859
one in which often is referenced

329
00:14:34,859 --> 00:14:37,199
during the Christmas season.

330
00:14:37,199 --> 00:14:38,659
But in Matthew chapter number one,

331
00:14:38,659 --> 00:14:41,859
when we think specifically of these prophecies

332
00:14:41,859 --> 00:14:43,819
of Isaiah seven and Isaiah nine,

333
00:14:43,819 --> 00:14:46,499
we find in Matthew chapter number one,

334
00:14:46,499 --> 00:14:48,819
the Bible says this in verse number 23,

335
00:14:48,819 --> 00:14:52,019
behold, a virgin shall be with child

336
00:14:52,019 --> 00:14:54,179
and shall bring forth a son

337
00:14:54,179 --> 00:14:56,699
and they shall call his name Emmanuel.

338
00:14:56,699 --> 00:15:00,879
Notice which being interpreted is God with us.

339
00:15:00,879 --> 00:15:03,419
Now we find that in verse number 22,

340
00:15:03,419 --> 00:15:05,099
the Bible says now all this was done

341
00:15:05,099 --> 00:15:07,019
that it might be fulfilled,

342
00:15:07,019 --> 00:15:10,899
which was spoken to the Lord by the prophet.

343
00:15:10,899 --> 00:15:14,539
And this was the announcement of the birth of Christ

344
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:17,099
and Joseph in verse 24,

345
00:15:17,099 --> 00:15:19,739
the Bible says then Joseph being raised from sleep

346
00:15:19,739 --> 00:15:22,859
did as the angel of the Lord had bidden him

347
00:15:22,859 --> 00:15:24,579
and took unto him his wife

348
00:15:24,579 --> 00:15:27,619
and knew her not till she had brought forth

349
00:15:27,619 --> 00:15:32,159
her firstborn son and he called his name Jesus.

350
00:15:32,159 --> 00:15:33,139
Wonderful.

351
00:15:34,479 --> 00:15:37,059
In Luke chapter number one,

352
00:15:37,059 --> 00:15:39,519
in verses 31 through 33,

353
00:15:39,519 --> 00:15:41,559
we read here of the fulfillment

354
00:15:41,559 --> 00:15:45,599
of what we had read there in Isaiah chapter number nine.

355
00:15:46,519 --> 00:15:47,819
In Luke chapter number one,

356
00:15:47,819 --> 00:15:51,119
we find the announcement with regard to the birth

357
00:15:51,119 --> 00:15:53,279
of not only the Messiah,

358
00:15:53,279 --> 00:15:56,059
but the birth of John the Baptist is recorded here.

359
00:15:56,059 --> 00:15:59,919
We do see the announcement and then of course his birth.

360
00:15:59,919 --> 00:16:02,919
We see in chapter two, as we've read just a moment ago,

361
00:16:02,919 --> 00:16:04,339
the birth of Christ,

362
00:16:04,339 --> 00:16:06,999
but I want you to notice in Luke chapter number one,

363
00:16:06,999 --> 00:16:09,119
during this announcement that is given

364
00:16:09,559 --> 00:16:11,639
at the beginning in verse number 31,

365
00:16:11,639 --> 00:16:13,039
the Bible repeats again,

366
00:16:13,039 --> 00:16:15,959
and behold, thou shalt conceive in thy womb.

367
00:16:15,959 --> 00:16:17,399
The angel of the Lord, we read verse 30,

368
00:16:17,399 --> 00:16:19,039
and the angel said unto her,

369
00:16:19,039 --> 00:16:24,039
fear not Mary, for thou hast found favor with God.

370
00:16:24,039 --> 00:16:27,279
And behold, thou shalt conceive in thy womb

371
00:16:27,279 --> 00:16:32,279
and bring forth a son and shall call his name Jesus.

372
00:16:32,799 --> 00:16:34,679
He shall be great.

373
00:16:34,679 --> 00:16:35,999
Isn't he so great?

374
00:16:36,759 --> 00:16:39,919
It says, and shall be called the son of the highest.

375
00:16:39,919 --> 00:16:42,799
And the Lord God shall give unto him the throne

376
00:16:42,799 --> 00:16:44,039
of his father, David,

377
00:16:44,039 --> 00:16:47,359
and he shall reign over the house of Jacob forever.

378
00:16:47,359 --> 00:16:51,639
And of his kingdom, there shall be no end.

379
00:16:51,639 --> 00:16:54,079
In the book of Micah chapter number five,

380
00:16:54,079 --> 00:16:56,759
God specifically provides a promise.

381
00:16:56,759 --> 00:16:59,479
When we think about the great promise of Christ's birth,

382
00:16:59,479 --> 00:17:02,279
we read in Micah chapter number five,

383
00:17:02,279 --> 00:17:05,639
the place where Christ would be born.

384
00:17:06,279 --> 00:17:07,959
If you read the book of Matthew,

385
00:17:07,959 --> 00:17:10,399
you'll find, and we'll look at that in just a moment,

386
00:17:10,399 --> 00:17:12,599
how that the heritage is like,

387
00:17:12,599 --> 00:17:15,119
hey, where is this one that's to be born?

388
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:18,279
And you see the prophecy here in Micah five.

389
00:17:18,279 --> 00:17:20,479
But in Micah chapter five, notice in verse number two,

390
00:17:20,479 --> 00:17:22,919
but thou Bethlehem Ephrata,

391
00:17:22,919 --> 00:17:26,499
though thou be little among the thousands of Judah,

392
00:17:26,499 --> 00:17:30,719
yet out of thee shall he come forth unto me

393
00:17:30,719 --> 00:17:33,039
that is to be ruler in Israel,

394
00:17:33,039 --> 00:17:37,479
whose goings forth have been from old, from everlasting.

395
00:17:37,479 --> 00:17:39,139
And in Matthew chapter two,

396
00:17:39,139 --> 00:17:43,639
we find that there as the Bible records for us,

397
00:17:43,639 --> 00:17:46,239
those wise men that arrived to Jerusalem,

398
00:17:46,239 --> 00:17:48,159
and they asked this question,

399
00:17:48,159 --> 00:17:50,959
where is he that is born King of the Jews?

400
00:17:50,959 --> 00:17:53,039
And they came to Jerusalem, they're seeking,

401
00:17:53,039 --> 00:17:56,839
and of course this caused a great ruckus there in Jerusalem

402
00:17:56,839 --> 00:17:58,759
and there's all sorts of things that took place

403
00:17:58,759 --> 00:18:01,599
and Herod, the king, he's troubled

404
00:18:01,599 --> 00:18:02,999
according to verse number three

405
00:18:02,999 --> 00:18:05,199
and all Jerusalem with him.

406
00:18:05,199 --> 00:18:07,599
But then notice in verse number four of Matthew two,

407
00:18:07,599 --> 00:18:10,239
the Bible says, and when he had gathered

408
00:18:10,239 --> 00:18:14,159
all the chief priests and scribes of the people together,

409
00:18:14,159 --> 00:18:16,599
let me explain to you just for a moment,

410
00:18:16,599 --> 00:18:18,239
in verse number four, what Herod does

411
00:18:18,239 --> 00:18:22,119
is he gathers together all of the religious leaders

412
00:18:22,119 --> 00:18:23,499
of the Jews.

413
00:18:23,499 --> 00:18:26,959
These religious leaders, these Jewish religious leaders,

414
00:18:26,959 --> 00:18:29,599
they would be very familiar

415
00:18:29,599 --> 00:18:33,919
with the Old Testament, experts of the Old Testament.

416
00:18:33,919 --> 00:18:35,919
And we find that he gathers them together

417
00:18:35,919 --> 00:18:38,299
and notice at the end of verse number four,

418
00:18:38,299 --> 00:18:43,299
he demanded of them where Christ should be born.

419
00:18:43,919 --> 00:18:45,779
The Bible says in verse number five,

420
00:18:45,779 --> 00:18:50,119
and they said unto him in Bethlehem of Judea,

421
00:18:50,119 --> 00:18:53,320
for thus it is written by the prophet.

422
00:18:53,320 --> 00:18:55,760
Isn't it sad that they knew the prophecy,

423
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,799
but they weren't looking for the Messiah.

424
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:01,079
They knew the prophecy,

425
00:19:01,079 --> 00:19:03,199
but they weren't looking for the Messiah.

426
00:19:03,199 --> 00:19:06,119
And in verse number six, they quote from Micah five,

427
00:19:06,119 --> 00:19:08,440
and thou Bethlehem in the land of Judah,

428
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:11,639
art not the least among the princes of Judah,

429
00:19:11,639 --> 00:19:13,419
for out of thee shall come a governor

430
00:19:13,419 --> 00:19:17,479
that shall rule my people Israel.

431
00:19:17,479 --> 00:19:19,079
So this morning, when we think about

432
00:19:19,079 --> 00:19:21,059
these good tidings of great joy,

433
00:19:21,059 --> 00:19:22,239
I want you to notice with me

434
00:19:22,239 --> 00:19:24,919
the great promise of Christ's birth.

435
00:19:24,919 --> 00:19:26,880
By the way, every promise of God

436
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:31,880
is sure, we can stand on the promises, amen.

437
00:19:32,399 --> 00:19:35,320
And I'm so thankful that our God cannot lie.

438
00:19:36,279 --> 00:19:40,779
He's given to us countless promises.

439
00:19:40,779 --> 00:19:42,239
As we look through the scriptures

440
00:19:42,239 --> 00:19:44,839
and we can claim them and we can embrace them

441
00:19:44,839 --> 00:19:49,519
and we can find that they will come to pass.

442
00:19:49,519 --> 00:19:51,959
Not only do we notice the great promise of Christ's birth,

443
00:19:51,959 --> 00:19:53,139
but number two, notice with me

444
00:19:53,139 --> 00:19:56,320
the great proclamation at Christ's birth.

445
00:19:56,760 --> 00:19:59,039
This was read earlier in Luke chapter number two,

446
00:19:59,039 --> 00:20:00,479
but let me just very quickly.

447
00:20:00,479 --> 00:20:03,819
make a couple of comments from Luke chapter number two,

448
00:20:03,819 --> 00:20:05,639
as we think about this great proclamation

449
00:20:05,639 --> 00:20:07,339
that was made at Christ's birth.

450
00:20:07,339 --> 00:20:09,919
There was a promise of Christ's birth,

451
00:20:09,919 --> 00:20:12,219
but now there's this great proclamation.

452
00:20:12,219 --> 00:20:14,539
It's the angel that makes the proclamation

453
00:20:14,539 --> 00:20:17,179
according to chapter number two in verse number 10.

454
00:20:17,179 --> 00:20:20,339
The Bible says, and the angel said unto them.

455
00:20:20,339 --> 00:20:22,559
And I think about this scene again,

456
00:20:22,559 --> 00:20:25,799
as you begin to wrap your mind around these verses

457
00:20:25,799 --> 00:20:29,279
of scripture that I read by way of introduction this morning

458
00:20:29,279 --> 00:20:30,759
and in your mind's eye,

459
00:20:30,759 --> 00:20:34,839
I hope that you can see the scene of what's unfolding.

460
00:20:34,839 --> 00:20:37,439
And again, they're out there like any other night,

461
00:20:37,439 --> 00:20:40,699
but there's this great stirring that takes place.

462
00:20:40,699 --> 00:20:42,879
And we find that the Bible tells us

463
00:20:42,879 --> 00:20:45,539
that an angel speaks to them.

464
00:20:46,919 --> 00:20:49,899
Notice what the angel proclaimed

465
00:20:49,899 --> 00:20:52,719
and the good tidings of great joy

466
00:20:52,719 --> 00:20:54,319
that are referenced in verse number 10.

467
00:20:54,319 --> 00:20:55,479
What is that?

468
00:20:55,479 --> 00:20:56,799
What is the greeting?

469
00:20:56,799 --> 00:20:58,119
Well, it's in verse number 11,

470
00:20:58,119 --> 00:21:03,119
the proclamation for unto you is born this day

471
00:21:03,359 --> 00:21:08,279
in the city of David, a savior, which is Christ the Lord.

472
00:21:09,399 --> 00:21:11,799
I want you to understand that this proclamation

473
00:21:11,799 --> 00:21:13,959
was made to these shepherds.

474
00:21:13,959 --> 00:21:16,759
I don't know how many of them were there

475
00:21:16,759 --> 00:21:18,359
and neither do you.

476
00:21:18,359 --> 00:21:20,259
It's plural, so it was more than one.

477
00:21:21,359 --> 00:21:24,079
We don't know how many shepherds were there,

478
00:21:24,079 --> 00:21:26,019
but however many were there,

479
00:21:26,019 --> 00:21:30,099
they received this glorious, this great proclamation

480
00:21:30,099 --> 00:21:31,799
of the birth of Christ.

481
00:21:31,799 --> 00:21:35,379
Can you imagine being the ones,

482
00:21:35,379 --> 00:21:39,299
however many of them there were that God saw fit

483
00:21:39,299 --> 00:21:42,199
to allow that angel to appear to them

484
00:21:42,199 --> 00:21:44,879
to deliver that message?

485
00:21:46,179 --> 00:21:48,339
But I want you to understand something very important

486
00:21:48,339 --> 00:21:49,479
in verse number 10.

487
00:21:49,479 --> 00:21:51,659
The Bible says, for behold,

488
00:21:51,659 --> 00:21:56,459
I bring you good tidings of great joy,

489
00:21:56,459 --> 00:22:01,459
which shall be, what's it say, to all people.

490
00:22:01,579 --> 00:22:04,939
This great proclamation at Christ's birth

491
00:22:04,939 --> 00:22:08,819
that we find was given by the angel to the shepherds.

492
00:22:08,819 --> 00:22:10,239
Yes, it was given to them,

493
00:22:10,239 --> 00:22:13,779
but it was not to be kept to themselves.

494
00:22:13,779 --> 00:22:16,299
This was a message that was given to them,

495
00:22:16,299 --> 00:22:19,219
but it was a message that was for all people.

496
00:22:19,219 --> 00:22:20,979
Isn't that a wonderful truth?

497
00:22:20,979 --> 00:22:24,099
I think about the glorious gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ

498
00:22:24,099 --> 00:22:26,419
and I was in my office this morning praying

499
00:22:26,419 --> 00:22:29,219
and just thanking God for having a Bible

500
00:22:29,219 --> 00:22:31,279
and for someone that shared the gospel with me

501
00:22:31,279 --> 00:22:35,259
and knowing the Lord Jesus Christ is my personal savior.

502
00:22:35,259 --> 00:22:37,959
And as I was rejoicing and just praising God

503
00:22:37,959 --> 00:22:39,139
for my own salvation,

504
00:22:39,139 --> 00:22:42,459
I was reminded that God saved us

505
00:22:42,459 --> 00:22:46,759
and God gave us the gospel not to keep it to ourselves,

506
00:22:46,759 --> 00:22:48,899
but to proclaim it to all people.

507
00:22:49,899 --> 00:22:54,259
These shepherds, they were given this great proclamation.

508
00:22:54,259 --> 00:22:56,939
They were the original recipients, if you will,

509
00:22:56,939 --> 00:22:59,539
of those that were on that hillside that night

510
00:22:59,539 --> 00:23:03,639
that heard this great proclamation by this angel.

511
00:23:03,639 --> 00:23:06,019
We find that there was a sign that was given

512
00:23:06,019 --> 00:23:07,499
according to verse number 12,

513
00:23:07,499 --> 00:23:09,459
and this shall be a sign unto you,

514
00:23:09,459 --> 00:23:13,459
ye shall find the babe wrapped in swaddling clothes

515
00:23:13,459 --> 00:23:16,539
lying in a manger.

516
00:23:16,539 --> 00:23:18,059
And it's interesting

517
00:23:18,059 --> 00:23:19,339
because when you see the scene,

518
00:23:19,339 --> 00:23:22,859
it almost seems to me as you read the text of Scripture,

519
00:23:22,859 --> 00:23:25,739
that almost as quickly as these angels arrived,

520
00:23:25,739 --> 00:23:27,739
this heavenly host arrives,

521
00:23:27,739 --> 00:23:30,959
almost as quickly as they come, they depart.

522
00:23:30,959 --> 00:23:33,379
For the Bible says in verse number 15,

523
00:23:33,379 --> 00:23:36,899
and it came to pass as the angels were gone away

524
00:23:36,899 --> 00:23:38,859
from them into heaven.

525
00:23:38,859 --> 00:23:41,539
I mean, the angels appeared, there's this great host

